cook: Cooking has been my hobby since I was a little girl. My first time in the kitchen, I made Kruntu kuku (coconut cake), and it turned out very tasty. As I grew older, I started making dishes as Bami goreng, Nasi goreng Since I was 15 years old, I always got asked to help in the kitchen, especially at parties. In June 2020, I started my own business called Food by Blessed Hands. Where I cook delicious Javanese, Chinese, Italian, Creole, and Surinamese dishes. - Mevis B Ceo of Food by blessed hands
